                <note rend="inline" type="source">693.006/38: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Johnson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-04-15T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >April 15, 1938—noon.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>125. Your 199, April 11, 2 p.m., in regard to possible curtailment by China of
                    unessential imports.</p>
                <p>You may orally and confidentially inform Young that the Department is confident
                    that, in connection with any measures which China may take for the protection of
                    her national economy, the Chinese Government would give due consideration to
                    American interests and would avoid any discrimination against those
                    interests.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
